Midgaard's charter registries cross-reference the Bell Synod in three ledger series: early oath-certification correspondence, Violet Compact witnessing contracts with a Rakuen satellite office, and sealed warrant authorizations routing displaced populations through Kel'Shadra intake.
The Continuity faction classifies the Synod as a defunct ecclesiastical institution under institutional succession law, placing it outside active administrative liability.
The Reckoning faction disputes this: the Synod's confession protocols were the mechanism by which Midgaard's resettlement testimonies were absorbed and routed to "below bell-line; no civic remainder" classification.
Midgaard commissioned the upstream displacement; the Synod provided the downstream disappearance mechanism.
The jurisdictional classification dispute determines whether Midgaard's role in the testimony suppression chain carries active legal obligation.

