Umbral archivists near the Gloamvault site preserved observation records tracking testimony submitted versus testimony returned, and the growing gap between those counts — the intake shadow.
The volume absorbed by the Synod that did not re-emerge in any form accessible to the submitting witness is substantial and internally consistent across Umbral records spanning the Synod's late institutional period.
