flags RAKUEN DELTARI
---
Deltari Reed Law requires witnessed measurement: a fact carries evidentiary weight only when two independent observers confirm it using the same calibration standard.
Bell Synod intake records fail this standard systematically: no external confirmation of what was submitted, no independent record of classification decisions, no counter-signature from any body outside the Synod hierarchy.
Under Deltari protocol, such records carry the status of internal memoranda, not legal testimony.
This classification has practical implications for suppression claims: the burden of proof for specific testimony disappearances falls on the submitting party's external evidence — which for Rakuen's resettled arrivals was often limited or destroyed as part of the same administrative process.
The Reed Law classification does not exonerate the Synod; it makes the evidentiary reconstruction harder for exactly the parties most harmed.
